A: I'm not sure what you mean by "in reverse order" but if you want to read the file in reverse order, you can use the RandomAccessFile class.
Here is an example of how to read the file in reverse order:
RandomAccessFile raf = new RandomAccessFile(file, "r");
raf.seek(raf.length());
int ch;
while ((ch = raf.read()) != -1) {
    System.out.print((char) ch);
}

This code opens the file in read-only mode and moves the file pointer to the end of the file. Then it reads the file in reverse order and prints the characters to the console.
